        <h3 id="docs-frames" class="docs-title">Frames</h3>
        <p>Use frames to create elements with defined aspect ratios.  All frames require the <code>.frame</code> base class and a modifier class to define their aspect ratio.  There is also a child element <code>.frame__inner</code> that is positioned absolutely and stretches the full dimensions of the frame.</p>
        <div class="row">
          {% assign ratios = '16x9 6x4 4x3 1x1 3x4 4x6 9x16' | split: " " %}
          {% for ratio in ratios %}
            <div class="col-lg-2 col-md-3 col-sm-4 col-xs-6">
              <div style="margin-bottom: 30px;">
                <div class="frame frame--{{ ratio }}" style="background-color: white; border: 1px solid #d8d8d8">
                  <div class="frame__inner flex-align-items-center flex-justify-center">
                    {{ ratio }}
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          {% endfor %}
        </div>
